{"cursor":"14381","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\nIn chemistry, 'recrystallization' is a technique used to purify chemicals. By\ndissolving both impurities and a compound in an appropriate solvent, either the\ndesired compound or impurities can be coaxed out of solution, leaving the other\nbehind. It is named for the crystals often formed when the compound\nprecipitates out.\n","linknr":248,"url":"Recrystallization_(chemistry)","recorded":1362486097,"links":33,"instances":["chemistry","chemistry","engineering_aspects","laboratory"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Chemical processes","Laboratory techniques","Phase transitions","Separation processes","Semiconductor growth"],"headings":["Chemistry","Ice","See also","References","Reference books","Gallery"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Snow_crystallization_in_Akureyri_2005-02-26_19-03-37.jpeg/200px-Snow_crystallization_in_Akureyri_2005-02-26_19-03-37.jpeg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4e/1_solvent_recrystallisation.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b3/Crystallization_Ibuprofen_Salt.JPG/220px-Crystallization_Ibuprofen_Salt.JPG","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6d/2_solvent_recrystallisation.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c4/2_solvent_recrystallisation_with_evaporation.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/27/Hot-filtration_1_solvent_recrystallisation.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/bf/X-ray_crystals_-_slow_evaporation_1_solvent.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6b/X-ray_crystals_-_slow_evaporation_2_solvent.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/55/X-ray_crystals_-_slow_gas_diffusion_2_solvent.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4f/X-ray_crystals_-_slow_liquid_diffu